<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 15:28:17 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>研究人员在科学上首次发现了人类在岩石艺术和洞穴墙壁上留下的古代 DNA</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-scientific-first-researchers-recovered-ancient-dna-that-humans-left-behind-on-rock-art-and-cave-walls-180989038/</link><description>洞穴壁上的 DNA 保存情况变化很大，但科学家表示，他们的工作是深入了解我们富有创造力的祖先的重要一步</description><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 14:27:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-scientific-first-researchers-recovered-ancient-dna-that-humans-left-behind-on-rock-art-and-cave-walls-180989038/</guid></item><item><title>在墨西哥丛林深处，考古学家发现了一座失落的玛雅城市，可能会提供有关文明崩溃前夕的线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/deep-in-the-mexican-jungle-archaeologists-discovered-a-lost-maya-city-that-may-yield-clues-about-the-civilization-just-before-it-collapsed-180989030/</link><description>研究人员砍伐了超过三英里的植被才能到达该地点，该地点位于熟悉的伐木路径范围之外。在那里，他们发现了独特的雕刻石碑和祭坛</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 21:44:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/deep-in-the-mexican-jungle-archaeologists-discovered-a-lost-maya-city-that-may-yield-clues-about-the-civilization-just-before-it-collapsed-180989030/</guid></item><item><title>观看有史以来在可见光下拍摄的最详细的银河系心脏照片，这将有助于天文学家寻找系外行星</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-most-detailed-photo-of-the-milky-ways-heart-ever-taken-in-visible-light-which-will-help-astronomers-hunt-for-exoplanets-180989027/</link><description>欧洲航天局的欧几里得望远镜是为了研究暗物质和暗能量而建造的，但去年的一天，它捕捉到了照亮我们银河系中心的密集恒星</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 21:09:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-most-detailed-photo-of-the-milky-ways-heart-ever-taken-in-visible-light-which-will-help-astronomers-hunt-for-exoplanets-180989027/</guid></item><item><title>历经多年打造，国家地理探索博物馆将带您踏上冒险之旅</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/years-in-the-making-national-geographics-museum-of-exploration-is-here-to-take-you-on-an-adventure-180989034/</link><description>翻新后的空间凸显了这个拥有 138 年历史的标志性品牌的标志，从野生动物摄影到人类学研究</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 20:03:24 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/years-in-the-making-national-geographics-museum-of-exploration-is-here-to-take-you-on-an-adventure-180989034/</guid></item><item><title>科学家破译了一部因维苏威火山喷发而冻结的 2000 年前哲学论文的残片</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-have-deciphered-the-surviving-fragments-of-a-2000-year-old-philosophical-treatise-frozen-in-time-by-mount-vesuvius-eruption-180989036/</link><description>这份纸莎草手稿是由火山灰保存下来的庞大图书馆的一部分。现在，剩余的段落——审视伦理、知识和人性——自公元 79 年以来首次可供访问</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 19:51:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-have-deciphered-the-surviving-fragments-of-a-2000-year-old-philosophical-treatise-frozen-in-time-by-mount-vesuvius-eruption-180989036/</guid></item><item><title>艺术太热？由于欧洲创纪录的热浪，巴黎一些博物馆和地标关闭或缩短开放时间</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/too-hot-for-art-some-paris-museums-and-landmarks-close-or-reduce-hours-amid-a-record-heat-wave-in-europe-180989029/</link><description>与此同时，其他机构也提供空调空间，为居民和游客提供避暑的方式</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 19:46:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/too-hot-for-art-some-paris-museums-and-landmarks-close-or-reduce-hours-amid-a-record-heat-wave-in-europe-180989029/</guid></item><item><title>诺曼·洛克威尔 (Norman Rockwell) 在白宫展出了数十年的彩色画作中捕捉到了西翼的喧嚣。他们现在首次出现在公众视野中</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/norman-rockwell-captured-the-hustle-of-the-west-wing-in-colorful-drawings-displayed-for-decades-in-the-white-house-theyre-now-on-public-view-for-the-first-time-180989025/</link><description>这些作品是为了在第二次世界大战最激烈的时期使富兰克林·罗斯福总统变得人性化而委托创作的</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 18:40:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/norman-rockwell-captured-the-hustle-of-the-west-wing-in-colorful-drawings-displayed-for-decades-in-the-white-house-theyre-now-on-public-view-for-the-first-time-180989025/</guid></item><item><title>早期人类可能在 180 万年前就已经使用了火，这几乎是已知最古老证据的年龄的两倍</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/early-humans-may-have-used-fire-1-8-million-years-ago-nearly-doubling-the-age-of-the-oldest-known-evidence-for-the-feat-180989015/</link><description>在南非的 Wonderwerk 洞穴中，人们在与直立人相关的泥土层中发现了烧焦的骨头。居民可能还没有掌握生火技术，但研究人员表示，他们可能已经移动并维持了自然火中的火焰</description><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 16:59:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/early-humans-may-have-used-fire-1-8-million-years-ago-nearly-doubling-the-age-of-the-oldest-known-evidence-for-the-feat-180989015/</guid></item><item><title>这些史前灵长类动物真的只是将雌性的尸体埋在洞穴深处吗？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-these-prehistoric-primates-really-bury-just-their-female-dead-deep-in-a-cave-180989020/</link><description>研究人员表示，迄今为止仅在南非地下发现的“纳莱迪人”骨骼化石缺乏关键的男性遗传标记</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 21:18:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/did-these-prehistoric-primates-really-bury-just-their-female-dead-deep-in-a-cave-180989020/</guid></item><item><title>委内瑞拉连续发生强烈地震，造成至少 188 人死亡。这是罕见“双峰”背后的科学原理</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/powerful-back-to-back-earthquakes-killed-at-least-188-people-in-venezuela-heres-the-science-behind-the-rare-doublet-180989018/</link><description>6月24日，两次7级以上地震袭击了该国北部地区，时间间隔仅39秒。虽然双峰序列在地震学中并非闻所未闻，但它们并不常见，尤其是在如此短的连续序列中</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 19:10:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/powerful-back-to-back-earthquakes-killed-at-least-188-people-in-venezuela-heres-the-science-behind-the-rare-doublet-180989018/</guid></item><item><title>密切关注德克萨斯州一只逍遥法外的网纹长颈鹿格雷西</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/keep-your-eyes-peeled-for-gracie-a-reticulated-giraffe-on-the-loose-in-texas-180989021/</link><description>这个高个子生物本月从一个私人牧场逃了出来，从那时起她就一直在德克萨斯丘陵地区漫游</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 17:57:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/keep-your-eyes-peeled-for-gracie-a-reticulated-giraffe-on-the-loose-in-texas-180989021/</guid></item><item><title>广岛幸存者遗失的回忆录被重新发现。现在，它将出版成书并改编成电影</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-lost-memoir-of-a-hiroshima-survivor-was-rediscovered-now-it-will-be-published-as-a-book-and-adapted-for-film-180989019/</link><description>近 80 年前，谷本清 (Kiyoshi Tanimoto) 记录了二战期间广岛原子弹爆炸的后果。他的手稿最近在美国图书馆被发现</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 17:24:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-lost-memoir-of-a-hiroshima-survivor-was-rediscovered-now-it-will-be-published-as-a-book-and-adapted-for-film-180989019/</guid></item><item><title>为什么这本248年前的笔记本上的字迹看起来很眼熟？原来是一本被遗忘的莫扎特手稿</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-the-handwriting-in-this-248-year-old-notebook-look-familiar-it-turned-out-to-be-a-forgotten-mozart-manuscript-180989017/</link><description>1778年，作曲家在担任导师期间，在学生的帮助下创作了七首长笛和竖琴短曲。这个月，观众第一次听到演出的作品</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 17:17:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/why-did-the-handwriting-in-this-248-year-old-notebook-look-familiar-it-turned-out-to-be-a-forgotten-mozart-manuscript-180989017/</guid></item><item><title>1.2亿年前，这种奇怪的长有羽毛的恐龙可能像飞鼠一样在树林间滑翔来捕食鸟类</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-strange-featured-dinosaur-may-have-glided-between-trees-like-a-flying-squirrel-to-hunt-birds-120-million-years-ago-180989011/</link><description>这种生物的化石提供了第一个证据，证明小盗龙生活在现在的中国西北部。它的发现也可能解开一个古老的谋杀之谜</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 16:04:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-strange-featured-dinosaur-may-have-glided-between-trees-like-a-flying-squirrel-to-hunt-birds-120-million-years-ago-180989011/</guid></item><item><title>灰鲸在旧金山湾遭到船只撞击。这种新的人工智能技术能拯救他们吗？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gray-whales-are-getting-struck-by-ships-in-san-francisco-bay-could-this-new-ai-powered-tech-save-them-180989009/</link><description>最近推出的系统包括两台热像仪，可以探测四英里外的灰鲸，让船只有足够的时间减速或改变航线，并避免撞上海洋哺乳动物</description><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gray-whales-are-getting-struck-by-ships-in-san-francisco-bay-could-this-new-ai-powered-tech-save-them-180989009/</guid></item><item><title>维京人真的是“不文明”的野蛮人吗？丹麦发现的大型纺织品生产基地挑战了刻板印象</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/large-textile-production-site-discovered-in-denmark-challenges-the-stereotype-of-vikings-as-uncivilized-barbarians-180989014/</link><description>这个占地超过 100 万平方英尺的大型定居点可能可以追溯到公元 600 年至 950 年的铁器时代晚期或维京时代早期</description><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 21:31:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/large-textile-production-site-discovered-in-denmark-challenges-the-stereotype-of-vikings-as-uncivilized-barbarians-180989014/</guid></item><item><title>据报道，一幅被盗的毕加索在巴黎附近的一次缉毒行动中刚刚出现，据报道是从一个存储设施中被盗走的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-stolen-picasso-just-turned-up-during-a-drug-raid-near-paris-reportedly-taken-from-a-storage-facility-180989010/</link><description>这幅画已被证实，但尚未透露。有报道称这是毕加索为玛丽·泰蕾兹·沃尔特创作的肖像之一</description><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 20:37:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-stolen-picasso-just-turned-up-during-a-drug-raid-near-paris-reportedly-taken-from-a-storage-facility-180989010/</guid></item><item><title>一项研究表明，星际彗星 3I/ATLAS 可能是太阳系中最古老的天体</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/interstellar-comet-3i-atlas-might-be-the-oldest-object-ever-seen-in-our-solar-system-a-study-suggests-180989007/</link><description>根据冰冷太空岩石喷出的气体成分，研究人员估计我们的客人可能有 120 亿岁——大约是太阳系年龄的三倍</description><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 19:55:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/interstellar-comet-3i-atlas-might-be-the-oldest-object-ever-seen-in-our-solar-system-a-study-suggests-180989007/</guid></item><item><title>世界上最古老的故事之一《奥德赛》通过人工智能生成的有声读物旁白（由奥斯卡获奖者的语音克隆）获得了现代诠释</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-odyssey-one-of-the-worlds-oldest-stories-gets-a-modern-spin-with-ai-generated-audiobook-narration-by-the-voice-clone-of-an-oscar-winner-actor-michael-caine-180989006/</link><description>与此同时，其他参与者正在反对在创意项目中使用人工智能，包括通过新的“人类同意”注册工具</description><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 18:56:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-odyssey-one-of-the-worlds-oldest-stories-gets-a-modern-spin-with-ai-generated-audiobook-narration-by-the-voice-clone-of-an-oscar-winner-actor-michael-caine-180989006/</guid></item><item><title>世界上第一个核时钟正在滴答作响，为研究暗物质和其他物理学之谜开辟了一条新途径</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-worlds-first-nuclear-clocks-are-ticking-opening-a-new-way-to-investigate-dark-matter-and-other-mysteries-of-physics-180989002/</link><description>两个独立的科学家团队创造了第一个功能时钟，可以利用放射性元素的原子核来保持超精确的时间</description><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 16:37:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-worlds-first-nuclear-clocks-are-ticking-opening-a-new-way-to-investigate-dark-matter-and-other-mysteries-of-physics-180989002/</guid></item></channel></rss>